{"title_page": "Smallholding", "text_new": "{{redirect|Smallholder|the British magazine|Smallholder (magazine)}}\n{{Globalize|date=December 2010}}\n\nA '''smallholding''' is a small [[farm]]. Smallholdings are usually farms supporting a single family with a mixture of [[cash crop]]s and [[subsistence farming]]. As a country becomes more affluent, smallholdings may not be self-sufficient but are valued primarily for the rural lifestyle that they provide for the owners, who often do not earn their livelihood from the farm. There are an estimated 500 million smallholder farms in the world, supporting almost two billion people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifad.org/operations/food/farmer.htm|title=Operating model \u2013 ifad.org|website=www.ifad.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-02|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505224355/http://www.ifad.org/operations/food/farmer.htm|archivedate=2013-05-05}}</ref> Today some companies try to include smallholdings into their [[Agricultural value chain|value chain]], providing seed, feed or fertilizer to improve production. Some say that this model shows benefits for both parties.<ref>{{cite web |title=Promising agribusiness |author=Christina Gradl|publisher=dandc.eu |date=March 2013 |url=http://www.dandc.eu/en/article/smallholder-farmers-and-retailers-benefit-intelligently-designed-value-chains|display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\n== Smallholdings in Britain ==\n\nIn [[British English]] usage, a '''smallholding''' is a piece of land and its adjacent living quarters for the smallholder and [[stable|stabling]] for [[Livestock|farm animal]]s.  It is usually smaller than a [[farm]] but larger than an [[Allotment (gardening)|allotment]], usually under {{convert|50|acre|ha}}. It is often established for breeding [[farm|farm animals]] [[organic movement|organically]] on [[free-range]] pastures. Alternatively, the smallholder may concentrate on [[market gardening|growing]] [[vegetable]]s by traditional methods or, in a more modern way, using plastic covers, [[polytunnel]]ing or [[row cover|cloches]] for quick growth.\n\nGenerally, a smallholding offers its owner a means of achieving [[self-sufficiency]] for its family's needs.   They may be able to supplement their income by selling surplus produce at a [[farmers' market]] or at a permanent [[Retailing#Shops and Stores|shop]] on the smallholding.\n\n== Hobby farms in Australia ==\nIn [[Western Australia]], many small acre farms were established under the [[Agricultural Land Purchase Act]] to encourage settlement. The government purchased large land grants held by absentee owners and subdivided them according to the best use for the land: the development of orchids in [[Coondle, Western Australia|Coondle]], viticulture, horse breeding, sheep grazing, and high density crops like corn, and broad acre crops like wheat.\n\nA [[hobby farm]] in [[Australia]] is a variety of smallholding that may be as small as 2 [[hectares]] up to a self-sustaining farm size, that allows the \"city farmer\" to have a house and a small number of animals or small crop fields or [[grape vine]]s. In Western Australia, they are often termed [[Special Rural Properties]] for planning purposes.\n\n== Lifestyle blocks in New Zealand ==\n\nIn [[New Zealand]], a [[lifestyle block]] is a smallholding valued primarily for the rural lifestyle it affords. Planning restrictions on subdividing farm land often lead to the creation of lifestyle blocks of minimum  permissible size near urban areas.\n\n== Developing countries ==\nIn many [[developing countries]], a smallholding is a small plot of land with low rental value, used to grow crops.<ref>Bunnett, R.B. (2002). ''Interactive Geography 4'', pp. 125, 315. SNP Pan Pacific Publishing. {{ISBN|981-208-657-9}}.</ref>  By some estimates, there are 525 million smallholder farmers in the world.<ref>Nagayets,Oksana (2005). [http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/sfproc.pdf The Future of Small Farms]. International Food Policy Research Institute and Overseas Development Institute Vision 2020 Initiative, p. 356.</ref>  Smallholders dominate production in certain key sectors such as coffee and cocoa.  Various types of agribusinesses work with smallholding farmers in a range of roles including buying crops, providing seed, and acting as financial institutions.<ref>International Finance Corporation (2013). Working with Smallholders: A Handbook for Firms Building Sustainable Supply Chains, p. 12. http://www.farms2firms.org</ref>\n\n===Thailand===\n{{see|Agriculture in Thailand}}\nIn 1975, there were 4.2 million smallholder farming households in Thailand. In 2013, Thailand had 5.9 million smallholder farming households. The average area of these smallholdings had shrunk from 3.7 hectares to 3.2 hectares over that period. Instead of farms getting larger and less numerous, as has been the case in the [[Global North]], the reverse happened: they got smaller and more numerous.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rigg |first1=Jonathan |title=Modern country, persistent smallholder: Explaining the puzzle of Thailand\u2019s truncated agrarian transition |url=https://theasiadialogue.com/2018/09/03/modern-country-persistent-smallholder-explaining-the-puzzle-of-thailands-truncated-agrarian-transition/ |website=The Asia Dialogue |publisher=University of Nottingham, Asia Research Institute |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Urban agriculture]]\n* [[Small-scale agriculture]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Allotments and Small Holdings|volume=1|pages=699\u2013704|first=Peter Anderson|last=Graham}} This provides an extensive historical and global view as of the early 20th century.\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wiktionary|smallholding}}\n* [http://www.deza.admin.ch/en/Home/Dokumentation/Videos/Item_227982 Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation's (SDC) videos on Smallscale and Family Farms Challenges and Opportunities]\n\n[[Category:Agriculture by type]]\n[[Category:Land management]]\n[[Category:Human habitats]]\n\n[[ms:Kebun kecil]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Smallholder|the British magazine|Smallholder (magazine)}}\n{{Globalize|date=December 2010}}\n\nA '''smallholding''' is a small [[farm]]. Smallholdings are usually farms supporting a single family with a mixture of [[cash crop]]s and [[subsistence farming]]. As a country becomes more affluent, smallholdings may not be self-sufficient but are valued primarily for the rural lifestyle that they provide for the owners, who often do not earn their livelihood from the farm. There are an estimated 500 million smallholder farms in the world, supporting almost two billion people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifad.org/operations/food/farmer.htm|title=Operating model \u2013 ifad.org|website=www.ifad.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-02|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130505224355/http://www.ifad.org/operations/food/farmer.htm|archivedate=2013-05-05}}</ref> Today some companies try to include smallholdings into their [[Agricultural value chain|value chain]], providing seed, feed or fertilizer to improve production. Some say that this model shows benefits for both parties.<ref>{{cite web |title=Promising agribusiness |author=Christina Gradl|publisher=dandc.eu |date=March 2013 |url=http://www.dandc.eu/en/article/smallholder-farmers-and-retailers-benefit-intelligently-designed-value-chains|display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\n== Smallholdings in Britain ==\n\nIn [[British English]] usage, a '''smallholding''' is a piece of land and its adjacent living quarters for the smallholder and [[stable|stabling]] for [[Livestock|farm animal]]s.  It is usually smaller than a [[farm]] but larger than an [[Allotment (gardening)|allotment]], usually under {{convert|50|acre|ha}}. It is often established for breeding [[farm|farm animals]] [[organic movement|organically]] on [[free-range]] pastures. Alternatively, the smallholder may concentrate on [[market gardening|growing]] [[vegetable]]s by traditional methods or, in a more modern way, using plastic covers, [[polytunnel]]ing or [[row cover|cloches]] for quick growth.\n\nGenerally, a smallholding offers its owner a means of achieving [[self-sufficiency]] for its family's needs.   They may be able to supplement their income by selling surplus produce at a [[farmers' market]] or at a permanent [[Retailing#Shops and Stores|shop]] on the smallholding.\n\n== Hobby farms in Australia ==\nIn [[Western Australia]], many small acre farms were established under the [[Agricultural Land Purchase Act]] to encourage settlement. The government purchased large land grants held by absentee owners and subdivided them according to the best use for the land: the development of orchids in [[Coondle, Western Australia|Coondle]], viticulture, horse breeding, sheep grazing, and high density crops like corn, and broad acre crops like wheat.\n\nA [[hobby farm]] in [[Australia]] is a variety of smallholding that may be as small as 2 [[hectares]] up to a self-sustaining farm size, that allows the \"city farmer\" to have a house and a small number of animals or small crop fields or [[grape vine]]s. In Western Australia, they are often termed [[Special Rural Properties]] for planning purposes.\n\n== Lifestyle blocks in New Zealand ==\n\nIn [[New Zealand]], a [[lifestyle block]] is a smallholding valued primarily for the rural lifestyle it affords. Planning restrictions on subdividing farm land often lead to the creation of lifestyle blocks of minimum  permissible size near urban areas.\n\n== Developing countries ==\nIn many [[developing countries]], a smallholding is a small plot of land with low rental value, used to grow crops.<ref>Bunnett, R.B. (2002). ''Interactive Geography 4'', pp. 125, 315. SNP Pan Pacific Publishing. {{ISBN|981-208-657-9}}.</ref>  By some estimates, there are 525 million smallholder farmers in the world.<ref>Nagayets,Oksana (2005). [http://www.ifpri.org/sites/default/files/publications/sfproc.pdf The Future of Small Farms]. International Food Policy Research Institute and Overseas Development Institute Vision 2020 Initiative, p. 356.</ref>  Smallholders dominate production in certain key sectors such as coffee and cocoa.  Various types of agribusinesses work with smallholding farmers in a range of roles including buying crops, providing seed, and acting as financial institutions.<ref>International Finance Corporation (2013). Working with Smallholders: A Handbook for Firms Building Sustainable Supply Chains, p. 12. http://www.farms2firms.org</ref>\n\n===Thailand===\nIn 1975, there were 4.2 million smallholder farming households in Thailand. In 2013, Thailand had 5.9 million smallholder farming households. The average area of these smallholdings had shrunk from 3.7 hectares to 3.2 hectares over that period. Instead of farms getting larger and less numerous, as has been the case in the [[Global North]], the reverse happened: they got smaller and more numerous.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rigg |first1=Jonathan |title=Modern country, persistent smallholder: Explaining the puzzle of Thailand\u2019s truncated agrarian transition |url=https://theasiadialogue.com/2018/09/03/modern-country-persistent-smallholder-explaining-the-puzzle-of-thailands-truncated-agrarian-transition/ |website=The Asia Dialogue |publisher=University of Nottingham, Asia Research Institute |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Urban agriculture]]\n* [[Small-scale agriculture]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Allotments and Small Holdings|volume=1|pages=699\u2013704|first=Peter Anderson|last=Graham}} This provides an extensive historical and global view as of the early 20th century.\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wiktionary|smallholding}}\n* [http://www.deza.admin.ch/en/Home/Dokumentation/Videos/Item_227982 Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation's (SDC) videos on Smallscale and Family Farms Challenges and Opportunities]\n\n[[Category:Agriculture by type]]\n[[Category:Land management]]\n[[Category:Human habitats]]\n\n[[ms:Kebun kecil]]\n", "name_user": "Seligne", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eThailand", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smallholding"}
{"title_page": "Miss K8", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Miss K8\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = Miss K8 at Summerburst 2016.jpg\n| birth_name       = Kateryna Kremko\n| alias            = {{hlist|Lady Kate|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.djguide.nl/djinfo.p?djid=9245&language=en|title=Biography Miss K8|website=DJ Guide|language=nl|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref>}}\n| birth_place      = [[Kiev]], Ukraine\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Techno]]|[[hardstyle]]|[[hardcore techno]]|[[gabber]]|[[Frenchcore]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|DJ|}} \n| label            = [[Masters of Hardcore]]\n| website          = {{url|missk8.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Kateryna Kremko''', known professionally as '''Miss K8''', is a female [[Disc jockey|DJ]] from [[Kyiv]], Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insomniac.com/artist/miss-k8|title=Miss K8|website=[[Insomniac (website)|Insomniac]]|language=en|access-date=2017-10-05}}</ref> Having played at music festivals such as [[Defqon.1 Festival|Defqon 1]] and [[Masters of Hardcore]], she gained recognition for her performances.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dancemag.cz/v-praze-zahraje-hardcore-ukrajinska-kraska-miss-k8/|title=V Praze zahraje hardcore ukrajinsk\u00e1 kr\u00e1ska MISS K8 - DanceMAG.cz|date=2014-01-15|work=DanceMAG.cz|access-date=2018-05-26|language=cs-CZ}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://alive-at-night.com/bossest-btches-in-the-harder-styles-our-leading-ladies/|title=Boss B*tches In the Harder Styles \u2013 Our Leading Ladies.|last=|first=|date=|work=Alive At Night|access-date=2018-05-26|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nShe released her debut single in 2012 titled \"Unforgettable\", which was released on the Masters of Hardcore record label. Her debut \"Divide & Conquer\" EP, which is a collaboration with [[Angerfist]] was released at the end of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hardstyle-industry.com/web/artists/Bio/255-Miss%20K8|title=Miss K8 - Biography|website=Hardstyle Industry|language=en|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref> In 2013, she released her ''Breathless'' EP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amsterdam-dance-event.nl/artists/miss-k8/18139/|title=Miss K8 - Artists - Amsterdam Dance Event|website=Amsterdam Dance Event|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref> In 2015, Miss K8 debuted on the Top 100 DJs poll by [[DJ Mag]] at 94.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hardcorenews.nl/artiest/miss-k8/|title=Miss K8 - Kateryna Kremko - Masters of Hardcore {{!}}{{!}} Hardcore News|work=Hardcore News|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL}}</ref> Her debut studio album ''MAGNET'' was released on 26 March 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.artofdance.nl/2016/03/01/miss-k8-album-release-at-masters-of-hardcore/|title=Miss K8 album release at Masters of Hardcore - Art of Dance|date=2016-03-01|work=Art of Dance|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324141809/http://www.artofdance.nl/2016/03/01/miss-k8-album-release-at-masters-of-hardcore/|archive-date=2016-03-24|url-status=dead}}</ref> She performed alongside Angerfist at the 2017 Escape Halloween festival by [[Insomniac (promoter)|Insomniac]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7897043/insomniac-escape-halloween-2017-lineup|title=Insomniac's Escape Halloween 2017 Announces DJ Snake, Marshmello, Jamie Jones, & More|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://partyflock.nl/interview/284:Miss-K8-Goddess-of-Hardcore-on-her-way-to-Olympus|title=Miss K8: Goddess of Hardcore on her way to Olympus|work=Partyflock|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.djoytech.com/djs/miss-k8/|title=Miss K8|date=2013-10-29|work=DJOYtech|access-date=2018-05-26|language=en-US}}</ref> Her track \"Raiders of Rampage\" featuring Nolz was ranked the #1 Hardcore track in the Masters of Hardcore Top 100 in 2016. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://djmag.com/topic-tags/miss-k8|title=Miss K8|work=DJ Mag|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> And in 2018, she received the #1 award for her track \"Out of the Frame\" in the Masters of Hardcore Top 100. <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hardcorenews.nl/en/this-is-the-masters-hardcore-top-100-2018/|title=This is the Masters of Hardcore Top 100 2018|work=Hardcore News|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref>\n\n\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|''Magnet''\n|2016\n|}\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|''Divide & Conquer'' <small>(with [[Angerfist]])</small>\n|2012\n|-\n|''Breathless''\n|2013\n|-\n|''The Poison''\n|2015\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|\"Unforgettable\"\n|2012\n|-\n|\"Metropolis of Massacre\" <small>(with MC Nolz)</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|-\n|\"New World Order\" <small>(with [[Angerfist]])</small>\n|-\n|\"Scream\" <small>(with [[Radical Redemption]] featuring MC Nolz)</small>\n|2016\n|-\n|\"St8ment\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|-\n|\"Resolute Power\" <small>(featuring MC Nolz)</small>\n|-\n|\"Temper\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|-\n|\"Out Of The Frame\"\n|-\n|\"Up In Smoke\" \n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|-\n|\"Elevate\"\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://missk8.com/ Official Website]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/missk8/ Official Instagram Account]\n* [https://soundcloud.com/missk8/ Profile on SoundCloud]\n* [https://www.allmusic.com/artist/miss-k8-mn0003211762 Profile on Allmusic]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian record producers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian DJs]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kiev]]\n[[Category:Techno musicians]]\n[[Category:Hardstyle musicians]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century women musicians]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian women record producers]]\n[[Category:Women in electronic music]]\n[[Category:Female DJs]]\n\n{{DJ-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Miss K8\n| background       = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image            = Miss K8 at Summerburst 2016.jpg\n| birth_name       = Kateryna Kremko\n| alias            = {{hlist|Lady Kate|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.djguide.nl/djinfo.p?djid=9245&language=en|title=Biography Miss K8|website=DJ Guide|language=nl|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref>}}\n| birth_place      = [[Kiev]], Ukraine\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Techno]]|[[hardstyle]]|[[hardcore techno]]|[[gabber]]|[[Frenchcore]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|DJ|}} \n| label            = [[Masters of Hardcore]]\n| website          = {{url|missk8.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Kateryna Kremko''', known professionally as '''Miss K8''', is a female [[Disc jockey|DJ]] from [[Kyiv]], Ukraine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insomniac.com/artist/miss-k8|title=Miss K8|website=[[Insomniac (website)|Insomniac]]|language=en|access-date=2017-10-05}}</ref> Having played at music festivals such as [[Defqon.1 Festival|Defqon 1]] and [[Masters of Hardcore]], she gained recognition for her performances.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dancemag.cz/v-praze-zahraje-hardcore-ukrajinska-kraska-miss-k8/|title=V Praze zahraje hardcore ukrajinsk\u00e1 kr\u00e1ska MISS K8 - DanceMAG.cz|date=2014-01-15|work=DanceMAG.cz|access-date=2018-05-26|language=cs-CZ}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://alive-at-night.com/bossest-btches-in-the-harder-styles-our-leading-ladies/|title=Boss B*tches In the Harder Styles \u2013 Our Leading Ladies.|last=|first=|date=|work=Alive At Night|access-date=2018-05-26|language=en-gb}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nShe released her debut single in 2012 titled \"Unforgettable\", which was released on the Masters of Hardcore record label. Her debut \"Divide & Conquer\" EP, which is a collaboration with [[Angerfist]] was released at the end of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hardstyle-industry.com/web/artists/Bio/255-Miss%20K8|title=Miss K8 - Biography|website=Hardstyle Industry|language=en|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref> In 2013, she released her ''Breathless'' EP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amsterdam-dance-event.nl/artists/miss-k8/18139/|title=Miss K8 - Artists - Amsterdam Dance Event|website=Amsterdam Dance Event|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref> In 2015, Miss K8 debuted on the Top 100 DJs poll by [[DJ Mag]] at 94.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hardcorenews.nl/artiest/miss-k8/|title=Miss K8 - Kateryna Kremko - Masters of Hardcore {{!}}{{!}} Hardcore News|work=Hardcore News|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL}}</ref> Her debut studio album ''MAGNET'' was released on 26 March 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.artofdance.nl/2016/03/01/miss-k8-album-release-at-masters-of-hardcore/|title=Miss K8 album release at Masters of Hardcore - Art of Dance|date=2016-03-01|work=Art of Dance|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324141809/http://www.artofdance.nl/2016/03/01/miss-k8-album-release-at-masters-of-hardcore/|archive-date=2016-03-24|url-status=dead}}</ref> She performed alongside Angerfist at the 2017 Escape Halloween festival by [[Insomniac (promoter)|Insomniac]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/7897043/insomniac-escape-halloween-2017-lineup|title=Insomniac's Escape Halloween 2017 Announces DJ Snake, Marshmello, Jamie Jones, & More|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://partyflock.nl/interview/284:Miss-K8-Goddess-of-Hardcore-on-her-way-to-Olympus|title=Miss K8: Goddess of Hardcore on her way to Olympus|work=Partyflock|access-date=2018-05-26|language=nl-NL}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.djoytech.com/djs/miss-k8/|title=Miss K8|date=2013-10-29|work=DJOYtech|access-date=2018-05-26|language=en-US}}</ref> Her track \"Raiders of Rampage\" featuring Nolz was ranked the #1 Hardcore track in the Masters of Hardcore Top 100 in 2016. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://djmag.com/topic-tags/miss-k8|title=Miss K8 DJ Mag|work=Hardcore News|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> And in 2018, she received the #1 award for her track \"Out of the Frame\" in the Masters of Hardcore Top 100. <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hardcorenews.nl/en/this-is-the-masters-hardcore-top-100-2018/|title=This is the Masters of Hardcore Top 100 2018|work=Hardcore News|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref>\n\n\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|''Magnet''\n|2016\n|}\n\n=== Extended plays ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|''Divide & Conquer'' <small>(with [[Angerfist]])</small>\n|2012\n|-\n|''Breathless''\n|2013\n|-\n|''The Poison''\n|2015\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n|-\n|\"Unforgettable\"\n|2012\n|-\n|\"Metropolis of Massacre\" <small>(with MC Nolz)</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|-\n|\"New World Order\" <small>(with [[Angerfist]])</small>\n|-\n|\"Scream\" <small>(with [[Radical Redemption]] featuring MC Nolz)</small>\n|2016\n|-\n|\"St8ment\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|-\n|\"Resolute Power\" <small>(featuring MC Nolz)</small>\n|-\n|\"Temper\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|-\n|\"Out Of The Frame\"\n|-\n|\"Up In Smoke\" \n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|-\n|\"Elevate\"\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://missk8.com/ Official Website]\n* [https://www.instagram.com/missk8/ Official Instagram Account]\n* [https://soundcloud.com/missk8/ Profile on SoundCloud]\n* [https://www.allmusic.com/artist/miss-k8-mn0003211762 Profile on Allmusic]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian record producers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian DJs]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kiev]]\n[[Category:Techno musicians]]\n[[Category:Hardstyle musicians]]\n[[Category:Electronic dance music DJs]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century women musicians]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian women record producers]]\n[[Category:Women in electronic musi